               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM BERRY</hi>. I am a cheesemonger, and live in Richmond-street, Marylebone—I lost a piece of bacon on 6th Dec.—I saw it again the follow<lb></lb>ing morning—it was mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">RICHARD COMPTON</hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, B</hi> 87.) On 6th Dec. I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner running down Carlile-place with something under his arm—he ran into a watering-place—I ran after him, and said, "What have you got here?"—he said, "Nothing"—I found this bacon by his side, covered with this hand<lb></lb>kerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I ran in the place; I did not know it was there.</p>
